  "prompt": "I have a problem with coupon set up. I have created a coupon in WooCommerce and I want it to be applied to the product on sale. I have also removed the check from the exclude sale item. But still it's not applying that coupon to products which are on sale. How can I fix it?",
  "response": "Here are several steps to troubleshoot and resolve the coupon application issue in WooCommerce:\n\n1. Coupon Configuration Checklist:\n```\n- Ensure coupon is active/published\n- Check coupon usage restrictions\n- Verify coupon start/end dates\n- Confirm product eligibility\n- Validate minimum/maximum spend requirements\n```\n\n2. Specific Troubleshooting Steps:\n```php\n// Check coupon settings in admin panel\n- Verify \"Allow sale items\" is checked\n- Confirm product categories match coupon restrictions\n- Check coupon type (percentage/fixed amount)\n```\n\n3. Diagnostic Code Snippet:\n```php\nadd_filter('woocommerce_coupon_is_valid', function($valid, $coupon, $discount) {\n    // Debug coupon application logic\n    error_log('Coupon Debug: ' . $coupon->get_code());\n    error_log('Sale Items Allowed: ' . ($coupon->get_exclude_sale_items() ? 'No' : 'Yes'));\n    return $valid;\n}, 10, 3);\n```\n\n4. Potential Solutions:\n```\n- Clear WooCommerce cache\n- Deactivate conflicting plugins\n- Ensure WooCommerce is updated\n- Check theme compatibility\n```\n\n5. Manual Coupon Compatibility:\n```php\nadd_filter('woocommerce_coupon_is_valid', function($valid, $coupon, $cart) {\n    // Force coupon to work with sale items\n    $coupon->set_exclude_sale_items(false);\n    return $valid;\n}, 10, 3);\n```\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these troubleshooting methods?",
  "temperature": 1.0,
